&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Hi, we’re CompanyCam.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a simple-to-use photo documentation and productivity app for contractors of all commercial and home services industries. Packed with intuitive functionality, CompanyCam facilitates unparalleled communication and accountability across a contractor’s entire business. We’re committed to providing a consumer-grade, game-changing experience that helps our users build trust within their company and with their customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But don’t let that corporate description fool you—the people behind our buttoned-up product are laid-back (but hardworking), genuine, and kickass, and you could be one of them!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1&gt;The Role&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a sharp, self-motivated, problem-solving &lt;strong&gt;Senior Infrastructure Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Infrastructure Engineer, you’ll work with a small team to build solutions in AWS that keep CompanyCam’s web and mobile applications humming. You’ll collaborate with product engineers to deploy new features and improve our existing infrastructure to make it more reliable, resilient, and secure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll bring depth in one or more of the following: database operations and performance tuning, search infrastructure (OpenSearch/Elasticsearch), or observability and monitoring. You&#39;ll help us scale and harden the systems that underpin CompanyCam&#39;s products as we grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have strong Infrastructure skills and experience in another area, we’d love to talk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Working At CompanyCam&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our engineering team is remote-first, spanning every timezone across the U.S. We welcome &lt;strong&gt;all backgrounds&lt;/strong&gt; and value capability over credentials; whether you have a CS degree, a high school diploma, or no diploma at all, if you’re skilled and collaborative, you’re welcome here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We partner with product teams who work in synchronized multi-week cycles with dedicated planning phases. Our team actively collaborates with these product teams while ensuring smooth operation and continuous improvement of our production systems. We share weekly updates to track goals and maintain alignment, while giving you the flexibility to manage your work in the way that works best for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Meetings are purposeful and few. We champion a healthy work environment where you can focus on quality work during your 8-hour day and then log off. Nights and weekends are for you, not for work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We Ask Of You&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must-haves&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are our non-negotiables:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Show up&lt;/strong&gt;: give us your best and have the bravery to do difficult but necessary stuff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grow up&lt;/strong&gt;: take responsibility, learn continuously, and have a growth mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do good&lt;/strong&gt;: treat your co-workers and our customers the way you want to be treated.&lt;/li&gt;
